    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Also, be aware that there is a wierd behavior that you can see with the e-commerce example : if you clear all filters or click again on a selected rating, the largest one would become the new selected one. That's because I use the Range connector which when no refinement is set, put its value to the largest range possible. \n> To avoid that we can compute an extra props that will say if there's refinements or not. Do you have any other ideas ?\n\nThe fact that the largest range is shown selected when there's no range selected is something we should do. Because it does represent the current search state. The user is free to handle this largest range as he wants, maybe with a \"Clear\" button or \"All\".\n",
